    "number": 1877,
    "state": "open",
    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "RFC: field: make `fe_equal` handle its documented bound",
    "user": {
      "login": "l0rinc",
      "id": 1841944,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDE5NDQ=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1841944?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/l0rinc",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/l0rinc/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "**Problem:** While reviewing this area with Fable, I noticed that `secp256k1_fe_equal(a, b)` says `b` may have magnitude up to 31, but that boundary does not actually work.\r\nA zero value carried at magnitude 31 can fail the comparison.\r\n\r\n**Alternative:** One possible fix is to lower the documented bound from 31 to 30, which would avoid adding work to `fe_equal`.\r\nI could not make that version produce a useful failing test, because magnitude 31 would become invalid input instead of a case `fe_equal` should handle.\r\n\r\n**Fix:** This keeps the existing documented bound and makes `fe_equal` handle it by normalizing the temporary value before adding `b`.\r\nThe new test compares canonical zero with zero stored at magnitude 31, and fails without the code change.\r\n\r\n**Review help wanted:** I would appreciate review on whether this is a real problem in practice and whether preserving the current bound is the right tradeoff.\r\n",
