      "message": "field: support fe_equal's full b magnitude\n\n`secp256k1_fe_equal(a, b)` promises to handle a second input with magnitude up to 31.\nBefore this change, an input at that limit could run out of internal headroom while comparing equal zero values.\n\nThe function first turns `a` into its opposite and then adds `b`.\nFor zero, that temporary form can already use extra headroom, so adding a maximum-magnitude `b` can exceed what the field code can safely carry.\nIn VERIFY builds this stops at an internal check.\nIn 10x26 non-VERIFY builds the oversized temporary can wrap and make equal zero values compare unequal.\n\nNormalize the temporary before adding `b`, which keeps the existing documented limit valid.\nAdd a focused test that compares canonical zero with a zero value stored at magnitude 31.",
